rmerly called sportsmedia technology corporation type private industry broadcast digital distribution event support founded  founder gerard j hall number of locations durham north carolina fremont california products computer software computer hardware number of employees  website httpwwwsmtcom smt formerly sportsmedia technology corporation pioneered the first realtime scoring and wireless data system on television the privately held company specializes in data integration technology and broadcast graphics that enhance broadcasts webcasts and live events in sports and entertainment smt’s customers include major broadcast television networks regional and specialty networks and sport governing bodies in  it acquired ids information and display systems as a division of the company to provide scoring results and statistics onsite for live events in  smt acquired chicagobased rival sportvision  contents  history  leadership  products  iso track  goto board  smart and augmented reality  clients  noteworthy events  awards  references  external links historyedit smt was founded in  by gerard j hall after developing the first realtime scoring and wireless data delivery system for the pga tour to replace walkietalkie communication used at the time “the scoring over walkietalkies was just really really problematic” hall recalled in  he developed a way to interface realtime scoring with tv production using personal computers hall provided this interface from  to  for nbc sports’ coverage of pga tour telecasts in june  he formally incorporated what was then known as sportsmedia technology corporation with an eye toward offering tv interface technology to other sports television broadcasters shortly thereafter sportsmedia technology signed an exclusive fouryear agreement with espn to provide interface tv graphics services for many live sporting events the scoring system used by sportsmedia became modified during this period to include compiling statistics based on performance or event data of a sports or performance event or activity the system received a us patent in  following the end of the exclusive espn contract hall led sportsmedia technology into the design and development of the first clockandscore graphic on tv the sportsmedia autograph device it became known as the fox box  as it came to prominence on nfl football telecasts on the fox network in  as a realtime scoreboard and it set constant onair graphic scoreboards as standard operating procedure for all sports telecasts by the late s sportsmedia technology began providing statistics for cbs sports announcers to use every year during broadcasts of the ncaa final four basketball tournament as well as shot clocks game clocks and scores that appear on screen beginning in  sportsmedia technology began providing graphics statistics world feeds and video enhancements to the annual super bowl broadcast for super bowl xlvii in  six cameras were calibrated with the first down line by smt in the early s sportsmedia technology moved into the virtual graphics realm with what it branded as “sports media augmented reality technology” smart its firstdown line product called smart virtual insertion publisher vip was used first by nbc sports in  for notre dame games to indicate where a football team had to cross on a field in order to score a first down smart vip provided the virtual firstdown line for monday night football coverage by abc sports in  in september  sportsmedia technology raised  million in outside capital to finance its expansion vicente capital partners a los angelesbased private equity firm received a minority ownership stake in the business as part of the deal sportsmedia technology changed its name to smt in january  the company said the name change reflected its expansion into other sectors besides sports such as entertainment education and medical looking for an acquisition that would add new products and services to its current product mix and help it expand its market reach smt acquired jacksonville flabased information and display systems llc also known as ids in february  in a deal that doubled the size of smt idss scoring and statistics systems and display boards and systems are used at such events as wimbledon the us open the french open and the australian open as part of the deal smt operated ids as a wholly owned business unit of smt while gerard j hall became ceo of both companies and remained as president of smt  smt launched a company called n designstudio in  to focus on motion graphic design and branding solutions clients include revolt tv food network fantasy sports network crossfit games nascar and the women’s tennis association in a deal finalized oct   smt acquired sportvision a company founded in  with more than  patents and best known for popular onscreen graphics like the yellow “st  ten” line in football the “pitchfx” virtual strike zone in baseball and the “racefx” pointer system in nascar the transaction was unanimously approved by smt’s board of directors and was financed through a minorityround investment by eldridge industries vicente capital partners and smt ceo gerard j hall leadershipedit gerard j hall serves as the founder president and ceo of smt upon graduation from harvard university in  he won the st andrew’s scholarship to attend scotland’s university of edinburgh where he pursued a master of science in computer science hall continued his graduate studies while teaching computer science at the university of central florida before leaving in  to work with the epson computer corporation he established what would become smt two years later hall was a  finalist for the ey entrepreneur of the year award in the southeast which includes alabama georgia north carolina south carolina and tennessee productsedit iso trackedit smts iso track software features an onscreen imagebased pointer graphic that identifies and tracks vehicles horses cyclists and athletes in realtime for events such as professional motorsports horse racing cycling stage races and marathons the imagerecognition tracking software does not require the traditional stationary camera and has been deployed for events including the indianapolis  the kentucky derby the tour de france and the new york city marathon goto boardedit smt’s goto board giant onair talent operated board is a large touchscreen monitor and analysis tool that announcers use to stop and pause video and draganddrop statistics it has been used both in sports and entertainment shows such as mlb network and the bet channel’s   park music video show smart and augmented realityedit smt’s smart system utilizes smt’s imagestitch technology to display graphics and signage within a live virtual scene smart line produces digital markers on a pitch such as the first down marker on a football field and smart vip displays onair graphics including signage billboards and video displays smart studio produces realtime d virtual studios for nbc sunday night football smt has provided augmented reality products such as night vision which can be used on replays to highlight the onfield action by blacking out the field around the players while retaining the yard markers clientsedit smt has provided data and social media for many regional and national tv channels including abc sports nbc sports cbs sports espn new england sports network turner sports tnt yes network noteworthy eventsedit sporting events that have used smt’s products include the super bowl the indianapolis  the kentucky derby summer and winter x games nba games nascar races nhl games awardsedit two  silver telly awards for video production and supporting virtual graphics  promaxbda sports marketing award  davey award tv sports referencesedit  httpwwwsportsvideoorgsvgexclusivesmtacquiressportvisioninmeetingofsportstechnologygiants  httpwwwvicentecapitalcomportfoliophp  httpswwwyoutubecomwatchvtkboeyem  httpsportsvideoorgmainconnectedsportsgerardjhallsmtpresidentandceo  httpswwwgooglecompatentsus 